"{\"abstract\":\"The success of any graph-based clustering algorithm depends heavily on the quality of the similarity matrix being clustered, which is itself highly dependent on point-wise scaling parameters. We propose a novel technique for finding point-wise scaling parameters based on Ripley's K-function [12] which enables data clustering at different density scales within the same dataset. Additionally, we provide a method for enhancing the spatial similarity matrix by including a density metric between neighborhoods. We show how our proposed methods for building similarity matrices can improve the results attained by traditional approaches for several well known clustering algorithms on a variety of datasets.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"2022033\",\"name\":\"K. Streib\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2022033\"},{\"authorId\":\"144429686\",\"name\":\"J. Davis\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/144429686\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"48561563\",\"name\":\"Mohamed Amgad\"},{\"authorId\":\"5772197\",\"name\":\"Anri Itoh\"},{\"authorId\":\"50503910\",\"name\":\"M. M. K. Tsui\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1371/journal.pone.0144404\",\"intent\":[\"background\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"4ea66006e972ae0fc32018fbc99e5b3fcfdbabca\",\"title\":\"Extending Ripley\\u2019s K-Function to Quantify Aggregation in 2-D Grayscale Images\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/4ea66006e972ae0fc32018fbc99e5b3fcfdbabca\",\"venue\":\"PloS one\",\"year\":2015},{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"48380565\",\"name\":\"Y. Z. Zhang\"},{\"authorId\":\"48752123\",\"name\":\"Y. Jiang\"},{\"authorId\":\"103214633\",\"name\":\"Zhi-Feng Pang\"}],\"doi\":\"10.4028/www.scientific.net/AMR.765-767.730\",\"intent\":[\"background\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"c8a4c4376f48dafd0b48ece6329e79ca34d919de\",\"title\":\"Cheeger Cut Model for the Balanced Data Classifi